## Code Standards

### Guard Clauses (MANDATORY)

```
// ALWAYS: Guard clauses with early return
function process(data) {
  if (!data) return null;
  if (!data.valid) return null;

  // Happy path at lowest indentation
  return transform(data);
}

// NEVER: Else blocks
function process(data) {
  if (data) {
    return transform(data);
  } else {  // FORBIDDEN
    return null;
  }
}
```

### No TODOs
- Fix immediately or delete
- No placeholder implementations
- No "coming soon" features

### No Mocking
- Real backend connections
- Real databases (use testcontainers)
- Real external services where possible

### No Utils/Misc
- Proper package organization
- Descriptive names
- Single responsibility

